File: President Cyril Ramaphosa. JOHANNESBURG - President Cyril Ramaphosa has written an impassioned letter about corruption to the African National Congress (ANC). Ramaphosa says the party should publicly disassociate itself from anyone accused of corruption. READ: WHO chief brands COVID-19 protection gear corruption 'murder He says that as the inheritors of the legacy of people such as Nelson Mandela and OR Tambo, the ANC has to be honest with the people of South Africa. Ramaphosa highlights that South Africans aren't protesting out of hatred, but because they feel betrayed. He ends the letter by saying that he intends, as leader of the ANC and as President, to end all forms of corruption. READ: BLF lays corruption charges against Ramaphosa Meanwhile, The Black First Land First has opened a case of corruption against President Cyril Ramaphosa at Hillbrow Police Station in Johannesburg. The party's leader, Andile Mngxitama has accused the President of misusing the R 500-billion COVID-19 relief fund. Read the letter by President Cyril Ramaphosa below: Letter to ANC Members (1) by eNCA.com on Scribd 